  "response": "In healthcare, RFP stands for \"Request for Proposal.\" It is a document used by healthcare organizations to solicit bids from potential vendors or service providers for specific products or services. The RFP outlines the requirements, specifications, and evaluation criteria that the organization uses to select the best proposal. This process helps healthcare organizations make informed decisions and secure the most suitable solutions for their needs.",
